I looked around a bit, there is no integer log 2 in Numpy.

Probably `np.log2` isn't fast for integers in the first place, and certainly the expression `(np.log2(uniq//4)) // 2` will not be fast because of temp Numpy array copies. So the first thing to do if speed matters here would be to move this to C with a simple implementation of `ilog2`(not using asm).

